l5p:pack_tcps_std a l5p:Pack ; l5p:packId "tcps-std-pack" ; l5p:wave l5p:wave1 ;
    l5p:standing l5p:InProgress ;
    l5p:currentCeiling "L2-L5 mixed (L5 Consumer-effort, L4 Generation-depth/Handler-gap/Regen-lifecycle/Target-API-fidelity, L3 Test-generation 1/1 real test, L2 Ontology-expressiveness). cap06 CLOSED 2026-07-22 (wave3 tcps-cluster cell, worktree wf_8730e757-e2c-1): packs/tcps-std-pack/templates/persistence_sabotage_proof.rs.tmpl projects 2 new tcps_std:PersistCase individuals via a real sparql: frontmatter into crates/tcps-std/tests/tcps_std_persistence_sabotage_proof.rs, which calls the REAL 受領証を保存する with a genuinely adversarial filesystem precondition (a 根 path whose parent component is a pre-existing regular file, so fs::create_dir_all fails with a real OS NotADirectory error) plus a positive control on a writable root. This crate's 受領証を保存する never branches on receipt field values -- io::Result on create_dir_all is its ONLY real conditional behavior -- so a 2-case suite is exhaustive here, not artificially thin (unlike tcps-core-pack's much larger guard-condition boundary-value space). A live self-check caught and fixed a real tautology bug during development: an earlier draft derived the filesystem precondition FROM tcps_std:expectedOutcome directly, so the constructed precondition always matched whatever outcome was declared and the assertion could never fail regardless of ontology content -- fixed by adding a SEPARATE tcps_std:rootScenario predicate that alone drives precondition construction, with expectedOutcome compared independently (see ontology.ttl's pscRootBlockedByFile comment). Non-vacuity re-verified against the FIXED template: flipped expectedOutcome Err->Ok with rootScenario unchanged, re-synced, got a real failure ('left: false, right: true ... returned Err(Os { code: 20, kind: NotADirectory ... })'), then restored byte-for-byte (pure-insertion diff confirmed) and re-synced to 2/2 green. Idempotent: second sync's live receipt reports both crates/tcps-std/Cargo.toml (needed a new [dev-dependencies] tempfile=\"3\" entry, added to tcps_std:manifestText) and the new test file as 'skipped: unchanged: content identical'; sha256 508961bc... identical across two independent full cycles. Full cargo test --workspace green throughout." ;
