    l5p:currentCeiling "same shape as tcps-ffi-pack. cap06 CLOSED 2026-07-22 (wave3 tcps-cluster cell, worktree wf_8730e757-e2c-1): packs/tcps-cli-pack/templates/dispatch_sabotage_proof.rs.tmpl projects 4 new tcps:CliCase individuals via a real sparql: frontmatter into crates/tcps-cli/tests/tcps_cli_dispatch_sabotage_proof.rs, which spawns the REAL compiled `tcps` binary (env!(\"CARGO_BIN_EXE_tcps\"), a genuine subprocess boundary crossing, not a re-implementation of main.rs's dispatch) and asserts its real exit code -- 3 known-subcommand positive controls (検査/版/環境, all exit 0, each transcribed from an actual `./target/debug/tcps <cmd>` run before being written into the ontology, not guessed) plus 1 adversarial case (an unrecognized subcommand `でたらめ`, which hits main.rs's own `_ => { 使い方(); ExitCode::from(2) }` fallback arm). 2/2 tests passing. Non-vacuity independently verified: flipped the adversarial case's tcps:expectedExitCode 2->0, re-synced, got a real assertion failure (actual exit code 2 != declared-wrong expectation 0), then restored byte-for-byte (pure-insertion diff confirmed) and re-synced to 2/2 green. Idempotent: second sync's live receipt reports the new test file 'skipped: unchanged: content identical'; sha256 aee77a83... identical across two independent full cycles. Scope note, disclosed: 検査's own internal conditional (二本柱が閉じている()) is NOT independently adversarial-testable through the CLI's argv surface, because its input (豊田生産方式::原初形()) is a hardcoded const fn with every field true -- no argv reaches a false branch, so this is the pack's only real refusal path reachable this way, and the 2-vs-1 case split is exhaustive of it, not artificially thin. Full cargo test --workspace green throughout (18+7+5+2+2 = 34 tests across the 4 tcps-* crates)." ;
