    l5p:currentCeiling "L1 Handler-gap (doc/lookup only, adjudicated below), L2 elsewhere, L3 Test-generation (18/18, CI-wired, re-run live 2026-07-22 -- corrects this entry's stale '12/12': 6 registry_proof + 12 full_coverage_proof tests, matching pack.toml's own 'L5-push round-4' 18/18 claim, which this entry had never picked up). cap05 CLOSED 2026-07-22 (L5 wave3, cell wasm4pm-catalog-structural) -- found ALREADY CLOSED, not merely not-applicable, same class of finding as cargo-cicd-pack's cap05 (this file, cargo-cicd-pack entry): `full_coverage_proof.rs.tmpl` (12 tests) cross-checks TWO independently-issued SPARQL projections against each other with zero hardcoded EXPECTED array (its own doc-comment: 'walks wasm4pm_facts_registry::{BREEDS, ALGORITHMS} ... via a SEPARATE SPARQL SELECT than breed_algorithm_registry.md.tmpl uses'); `registry_artifact_proof.rs.tmpl` (6 tests) is, by its own documented design, a deliberately-kept hand-transcribed anti-tautology twin ('WITHOUT ever re-running the SPARQL that produced the artifact -- so none of these assertions can be tautological') -- the same hand-proof-plus-SPARQL-proof coexistence pattern star-toml-pack's cap05 closure established as acceptable, not a gap. Independently re-verified this pass: 18/18 re-run green; a real reversible drift test performed jointly with wasm4pm-algorithms-pack (see that entry) also exercised this pack's regeneration path end to end (wasm4pm_facts_registry.rs / full_coverage_proof.rs / BREED_ALGORITHM_REGISTRY.md all regenerated) -- all 18 tests stayed green through the edit and the revert. Handler-gap (cap02) adjudicated: genuinely, legitimately structural-N/A / L1-terminal by design, CONFIRMED (not merely asserted) by reading the generated code directly -- `src/wasm4pm_facts_registry.rs`'s `lookup_breed`/`lookup_algorithm`/`algorithms_by_category`/`breed_count`/`algorithm_count` are pure in-memory linear-search accessors over static `BREEDS`/`ALGORITHMS` tables: zero external calls, zero