    l5p:nextPromotionObligation "cap05 closed 2026-07-22 (see currentCeiling). Handler-gap adjudicated legitimately N/A/L1-terminal for THIS pack specifically (see currentCeiling) -- do not force a fabricated dispatch surface onto a pure fact-registry pack merely to move a number; the honest ceiling is that cap02 as a WHOLE still doesn't close, for the same shared reason as every other receiptctl-wired pack (src/lib.rs's hand-written `include!(\"ggen_pack_mods.rs\")` plus hand-written `pub mod verbs;`/`run()` -- see wasm4pm-algorithms-pack's entry and praxis-core-pack's cell-b investigation, this file's praxis-core-pack entry), not a defect unique to this pack. Also re-confirmed, already-disclosed by this pack's own WIRING.md (not this pass's discovery): the bundled `ontology/rules/breed_standing.n3` law rule is NOT activated in examples/receiptctl -- `grep -n law examples/receiptctl/ggen.toml` returns nothing -- so every breed row in the committed consumer renders the `ADMITTED` placeholder rather than the law-derived `EvidenceBound` standing; relevant to Consumer-effort/cap01 more than cap02. 5 capabilities remain genuinely unaudited this pass: cap06, cap08, cap09, cap10, cap11. Same cap09 reconciliation flag as wasm4pm-algorithms-pack's entry applies here too (see that entry) -- not unilaterally closed here, out of this cell's assigned-pack authority to decide for the other packs the same argument would touch." .
