    l5p:standing l5p:InProgress ;
    l5p:currentCeiling "L2 ceiling, L3 Test-generation (22/22, CI-wired, re-run live 2026-07-22). cap05 CLOSED 2026-07-22 (L5 wave3, cell wasm4pm-catalog-structural) -- found ALREADY CLOSED, not merely not-applicable, same class of finding as cargo-cicd-pack's cap05: independently read all 3 proof templates directly -- algorithms_catalog_proof.rs.tmpl, algorithms_invocation_dispatch_proof.rs.tmpl, algorithms_target_fidelity_proof.rs.tmpl -- each carries a real `sparql:` frontmatter with a from-scratch Tera for-loop building EXPECTED_TOTAL/EXPECTED_CATEGORY_COUNTS/the full-field per-row block and COMPOSABLE, no hand-typed EXPECTED array (2 of 16 catalog-proof tests are deliberately-kept named anti-tautology regression cases, matching star-toml-pack's kept-hand-transcribed-twin precedent, not the primary coverage mechanism). Verified non-vacuous with a real, reversible drift test (not just frontmatter inspection): edited `pi:Algo_inductive_miner`'s `pi:category` from `discovery` to `conformance` in this pack's ontology.ttl AND its verbatim mirror in wasm4pm-facts-pack/ontology.ttl (required together -- editing only one side correctly tripped `gates/020_single_valued.rq` then `gates/030_value_constraints.rq` via [FM-PACK-013] against the union graph receiptctl builds from all 6 wired packs, proving those cross-pack consistency gates are real and live, not decorative); re-synced (after the documented FM-PACK-008 ggen.lock re-lock and 5 FM-WRITE-005 stale-target deletions, not force:true) and confirmed the regenerated `CATALOG` const's `category` field AND the regenerated proof's `EXPECTED_CATEGORY_COUNTS` aggregate (conformance 4->5, discovery 20->19) and per-row assertion changed together automatically with zero hand edits to the test file; all 40 cross-pack tests (22 here + 18 in wasm4pm-facts-pack) green against the NEW value; reverted both ontology.ttl files byte-for-byte (git checkout, confirmed empty diff -- a first revert attempt via an unscoped `sed` accidentally flipped 4 unrelated legitimate `conformance` rows per file back to `discovery` too and was caught via `git diff` before being synced, then corrected via `git checkout`), re-synced, re-tested: 40/40 green, idempotent second sync (`git status` clean), receipt valid+signed. Handler-gap (cap02) adjudicated, NOT structurally N/A (correcting this entry's own prior note): `src/w4pm_algorithms_invocation_dispatch.rs` + its 3/3-passing proof is a real dispatch surface, not catalog-only -- `dispatch_verified()` makes a genuine compiled call into the pinned `wasm4pm-compat` crate's own `discover_ocel_dfg` (respecting CLAUDE.md's process-intelligence-boundary rule -- no local reimplementation) for the 1 of 60 rows carrying `pi:verifiedAgainst`, and typed-refuses (`DispatchError::NotComposable`) the other 59 rather than stubbing/panicking. This has existed since commit ad9106702 (predates wave1) but `.specify/maturity.ttl`'s own `mat:cg_003` `d2`/`l2` score ('L2 catalog only, no calls') was stale -- `git blame` confirms the score row and this dispatch template landed in the SAME commit, so the score never accounted for the file that shipped beside it; corrected in maturity.ttl this pass to L2->L3 with the same evidence." ;
