    l5p:nextPromotionObligation "cap05 closed 2026-07-22 (see currentCeiling), verified with a real live drift test, not just template inspection. cap02 (Handler-gap) is real-but-narrow, not zero and not N/A: the one composable dispatch arm requires no pack-specific hand-written domain logic (the behavior lives entirely in the pinned external crate), but the other 59/60 rows are structurally unreachable (wasm4pm itself cannot be a native dependency per CLAUDE.md's process-intelligence-boundary rule), not merely undone -- so this pack cannot single-handedly close cap02 by adding more dispatch arms. The wider cap02 gate this pack shares with every other receiptctl-wired pack is the consumer's own lib.rs: `include!(\"ggen_pack_mods.rs\")` plus hand-written `pub mod verbs;`/`run()` (independently re-confirmed by reading examples/receiptctl/src/lib.rs directly this pass) -- same generic seam praxis-core-pack's cell-b investigation already named (this file's praxis-core-pack entry: 'no accepted precedent anywhere in this repo for a single include! line closing cap02'), not a defect specific to this pack. 5 capabilities remain genuinely unaudited this pass: cap06, cap08, cap09, cap10, cap11. Note for reconciliation (not closed here, out of this cell's assigned-pack scope): `ggen receipt verify` against examples/receiptctl (which wires this pack) returned valid:true/signed:true/signature_valid:true this pass, using the SAME guard-pack-proofs.sh mechanism praxis-core-pack's cap09 closure (commit f944775ba) cited as sufficient for cap09 -- that argument, if sound, would generalize to every pack wired into any of guard-pack-proofs.sh's 4 CONSUMERS (this pack, wasm4pm-facts-pack, clap-noun-verb-pack, chicago-tdd-tools-pack, wasm4pm-cognition-pack, wasm4pm-compat-pack via receiptctl; star-toml-pack; cargo-cicd-pack), yet only praxis-core-pack's entry reflects it -- flagging the inconsistency for whoever reconciles cap09 across packs rather than closing it unilaterally here." .
