    l5p:currentCeiling "L2 ceiling, L3 Test-generation (17/17, CI-wired via guard-pack-proofs.sh, real behavioral proof). cap06 CLOSED 2026-07-21 (commit da278d798, cherry-picked from worktree cell-d's 083051c49): packs/wasm4pm-compat-pack/templates/wasm4pm_compat_events_proof.rs.tmpl extends the one incidental DanglingEventObjectLink witness into a systematic sabotage suite covering all 5 real OcelRefusal variants the pinned wasm4pm-compat =26.6.29 crate declares (src/ocel.rs, confirmed against the exact crates.io registry checkout at that version) -- DanglingEventObjectLink (pre-existing) plus 4 new: EmptyEventObjectLinks (via LinkedOcel::admit, same gate as the existing test), MissingReferenceObject, MultipleReferenceObjects, and ViolatesLocalityPrinciple (all three via OcelLog::validate_gianola_2026_locality). Each new test starts from this pack's own generated emit_* output, same pattern as the pre-existing test. Independently re-verified in this reconciliation pass (not just re-running the cell's claim): ran `cargo test -q --test wasm4pm_compat_events_proof` fresh after cherry-picking -- 17/17 passing; re-probed non-vacuity myself by reverting the MultipleReferenceObjects sabotage condition (removing the extra event-object link) and re-running that single test -- it genuinely failed, then was restored byte-for-byte and the full 17/17 suite passed again. Idempotent: second `ggen sync run` reports no diff in src/tests/docs. Scope note: cap06's capDesc also names \"compile-fail\" fixtures as a distinct sub-modality; none were added here -- only refusal-path/adversarial-input coverage is closed, not a trybuild-style compile-fail suite." ;
