    l5p:nextPromotionObligation "cap12 investigated 2026-07-21 (l5-wave3, wasm4pm-cognition cell) -- the premise that consumer replacement is 'structurally blocked without a native-callable reference' was checked against real source and found FALSE, not confirmed: `wasm4pm-cognition` v26.7.1 (crates.io, BUSL-1.1) exposes `breeds::dispatch::dispatch_breed(breed: &str, input: &BreedInput) -> Result<BreedOutput, String>` as plain native Rust with zero wasm-bindgen coupling -- `src/wasm.rs`'s `#[wasm_bindgen]` layer (the only reference the pack's own handler doc comment and .specify/maturity.ttl's mat:cg_004/d5 previously cited) is a thin JS bridge built ON TOP of that native core (wasm.rs imports dispatch_breed, not the reverse), confirmed by reading the crate's own registry-cached Cargo.toml (`wasm = [\"dep:wasm-bindgen\", \"dep:serde-wasm-bindgen\", \"dep:js-sys\"]` is a non-default optional feature; `default = [\"actor-ed25519\"]`) and breeds/mod.rs (`BreedInput`/`BreedOutput` both `#[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)]`). This exact workspace already depends on it natively: crates/praxis-graphlaw/Cargo.toml's `cognition` feature (`wasm4pm-cognition = { version = \"26.7.1\", optional = true }`, license-flagged BUSL-1.1, off by default -- 'Do NOT add `cognition` to any default feature list without re-clearing this license first') and crates/praxis-graphlaw/src/chatman/engine.rs:2133's `consult_breed` calling `dispatch_breed` directly. Verified live, not just read: a standalone probe crate built at /tmp (outside this workspace, `cargo run --offline` against the already-cached registry copy, zero license/dependency-graph entanglement with ggen) exercised a `serde_json` adapter matching this pack's exact freeze-slot signature (`breed_id: &str, input_json: &str) -> Result<String, String>`) and round-tripped a real MYCIN dispatch: non-empty `inference_trace` (1 step, satisfying the crate's own FM-5 fraud guard on empty traces), a derived+conformance-checked OCEL log, `selected=\"therapy=penicillin\"`; plus two real negative paths -- an unrecognized breed id fails with `\"unknown breed: not_a_real_breed_xyz\"`, a known breed (mycin) with an unmet precondition (zero rules) fails with `\"mycin: precondition failed: MYCIN requires at least one rule\"`. NOT marking Incompatible: that standing requires a mechanically proven closure impossibility, and this proof runs the opposite direction -- a working native bridge, not an absent one. cap12 remains open, NOT closed by this finding: the real remaining chain is (1) a license-policy adjudication this cell cannot make unilaterally (BUSL-1.1 is non-OSI; the same 're-clear the license first' caution praxis-graphlaw's own Cargo.toml states applies to any wasm4pm-cognition-pack consumer wiring this in); (2) once cleared, a real `serde_json` adapter in the freeze-slot handler body -- mechanical, not a research problem, since both types already derive Serialize/Deserialize; (3) a full consumer example (mirroring examples/praxis-core-verify) proving delete-and-regenerate yields a working, tested, receipted result, which is cap12's actual bar, not merely that dispatch works in isolation. 6 capabilities remain open: cap02 (adjudicate -- same Handler-gap posture as wasm4pm-facts-pack/wasm4pm-algorithms-pack: the freeze-slot handler is deliberately hand-completed by this pack's own documented design, pack.toml's own words), cap06, cap08, cap09, cap10, cap11 -- none audited this pass." .
