    l5p:nextPromotionObligation "cap05 and cap09 closed 2026-07-21 (see currentCeiling). 5 capabilities remain open: cap02, cap06, cap08, cap10, cap11. Cell-b's investigation this pass (not yet closing any of these, but narrowing next steps): cap02 -- examples/receiptctl's src/lib.rs still needs one hand-written `include!(\"ggen_pack_mods.rs\")` line plus hand-written `pub mod verbs;`/`run()`; pack_clap_noun_verb's own missingCap still lists cap02 too -- no accepted precedent anywhere in this repo for a single include! line closing cap02. cap06 -- one real but thin existing check (`generated_table_rejects_unknown_scenario_name`, closer to a sanity check than a systematic sabotage suite); wasm4pm-compat-pack's cap06 closure this same wave (see l5p:pack_wasm4pm_compat) is the pattern to reapply here. cap08 -- the sync receipt's closure map hashes every ontology/template file touched globally per sync run, not a per-artifact trace keyed to each generated file -- needs a provenance manifest or per-file header. cap10 -- no packaging/CI templates exist for this pack; would need new template categories (cf. tcps-release-pack's CI-YAML generation). cap11 -- no diffing tool exists; only demonstrated that a live ontology edit propagates through re-sync, not that it surfaces as a semantic diff with a no-manual-repair guarantee. This pack remains the reference implementation for wave2's reusable SPARQL-derived-proof pattern (see l5p:wave2 l5p:waveDesc)." .
