    l5p:currentCeiling "L2 ceiling, L3 Test-generation (12/12: 7 pre-existing hand-transcribed + 5 new SPARQL-derived, real regex/toml exercise); Target-API-fidelity UNVERIFIED. cap05 CLOSED 2026-07-21 (commit c3fae8346, cherry-picked from worktree cell-e's a8fe5661c): applies praxis-core-pack's cap05 reference pattern to lsp-max-pack's own lm:LintRule ontology shape. Unlike praxis-core-pack/star-toml-pack, neither of this pack's generated-source templates carries a freeze_policy key -- the real gap closed here is that rule_pack_proof.rs.tmpl's EXPECTED_RULES literal lives in the template's own Rust source text (no sparql: key at all), so it only changes on a hand-edit, never automatically from an ontology.ttl edit. Added rule_pack_sparql_derived_proof.rs.tmpl (real sparql: frontmatter, identical `rules` query to rule_pack.toml.tmpl, no freeze_policy, a from-scratch Tera for-loop building a LIVE_RULES array). Built examples/lsp-max-verify/ (no pre-existing consumer existed). Independently re-verified in this reconciliation pass (not just re-running the cell's claim): ran `cargo test -q` fresh after cherry-picking -- 7/7 + 5/5 = 12/12, matching the cell's counts exactly; independently reproduced the full drift-sensitivity experiment myself end to end (not merely re-reading the report): changed UnwrapRule's lm:severity from \"error\" to \"warning\" in ontology.ttl, hit and remediated the same two documented gate refusals the cell hit (FM-PACK-008 stale ggen.lock hash -- deleted to re-lock; FM-WRITE-005 differing-target refusal on 3 separate targets in turn -- deleted each stale target, no force:true used), then confirmed the new proof's LIVE_RULES re-derived to \"warning\" and passed (5/5) while the pre-existing hand-transcribed proof failed with the exact reported message (\"severity mismatch for LSPMAX-UNWRAP-001, left: \\\"warning\\\", right: \\\"error\\\"\"); reverted ontology.ttl byte-for-byte (confirmed via git diff empty), re-locked, re-synced twice (files_generated=0 on the second run, confirming idempotency), and confirmed all 12 tests green again with a clean working tree." ;
