l5p:pack_rmcp a l5p:Pack ; l5p:packId "rmcp-pack" ; l5p:wave l5p:wave5 ;
    l5p:standing l5p:InProgress ;
    l5p:currentCeiling "L2-L3 domain-pack ceiling: single external crate (rmcp, github.com/modelcontextprotocol/rust-sdk, crates.io `rmcp = \"2.2\"`), source-audited 2026-07-21 by `cargo add rmcp --features server,client,macros,transport-io,transport-child-process` + `cargo fetch` into ~/.cargo/registry/src/.../rmcp-2.2.0/ and reading that vendored source directly, not docs.rs prose or ~/remo/rmcp (confirmed empty of Cargo.toml/src). 72 ontology individuals: 43 rmcp:HandlerMethod (all 27 ServerHandler + all 16 ClientHandler trait methods), 7 rmcp:Macro, 7 rmcp:Transport, 15 rmcp:Feature -- reconfirmed by direct grep of ontology.ttl this census pass. Test count 26/26, reconfirmed live this pass (`cargo test -q` in examples/rmcp-verify): 12 hand-transcribed (rmcp_handler_catalog_proof.rs, anti-tautology discipline, no sparql: frontmatter) + 5 real-behavior (rmcp_stub_handler_proof.rs, instantiates RmcpStubHandler and asserts on a real rmcp::model::Tool returned by the actual compiled crate) + 4 SPARQL-derived (cap05) + 5 refusal-path/adversarial-input (cap06). Six of 12 capabilities closed. cap03 (deterministic regen) -- CLOSED, re-verified live this pass: repeated `ggen sync run` after every edit reports `skipped: unchanged: content identical` for every freeze_policy:checksum output; the sole force:true output (src/rmcp_lib_wiring.rs) is byte-identical every re-sync (confirmed via git diff). cap04 (fixed-point convergence) -- CLOSED 2026-07-21 (commit fcff3b05c): deleted every generated file in examples/rmcp-verify (all of src/*.rs except the hand-written src/lib.rs, all of tests/, all of docs/) plus .ggen/freeze/rmcp-pack, ran one `ggen sync run` from that near-empty state -- all outputs `written`, byte-identical to the committed tree (git status --short empty), 26/26 tests passing against the freshly-rebuilt files. cap05 (generated verification) -- CLOSED 2026-07-21 (commit e8e61e8dc): packs/rmcp-pack/templates/rmcp_handler_catalog_sparql_derived_proof.rs.tmpl reapplies praxis-core-pack/star-toml-pack's wave-2 pattern -- real sparql: frontmatter (identical server_rows/client_rows queries to rmcp_handler_catalog.rs.tmpl), no freeze_policy, LIVE_SERVER_ROWS/LIVE_CLIENT_ROWS baked fresh every sync and asserted against src/rmcp_handler_catalog.rs's actual on-disk text via include_str!. Drift-sensitivity independently verified live: temporarily edited rmcp:server-call-tool's rmcp:defaultBehavior and re-synced -- the old hand-transcribed proof failed exactly as predicted (`assertion failed: row.default_behavior.contains(\"CallToolResult::error\")`) while the new proof stayed 4/4 green against the changed live value; reverted byte-for-byte (git diff empty), pack hash matched pre-edit, 26/26 green again. cap06 (generated negative witnesses) -- CLOSED 2026-07-21 (commit e8e61e8dc): rmcp_default_handler_proof.rs.tmpl defines RmcpDefaultHandler with zero method overrides -- `impl ServerHandler for RmcpDefaultHandler {}` compiles because rmcp-2.2.0's own src/handler/server.rs:432-434 declares the entire trait body as one `server_handler_methods!()` macro invocation, confirmed by reading the real vendored source -- then calls the real, sync `get_tool()` default body and asserts `None` for an unregistered name, an empty name, and an adversarial path-traversal/injection-shaped name against the actual compiled rmcp crate, covering the refusal-path and adversarial-input sub-modalities. Compile-fail sub-modality independently verified live too: renamed rmcp:server-get-tool's methodName in the ontology, resynced, got a real `error[E0425]: cannot find value LIVE_GET_TOOL_DEFAULT_BEHAVIOR in this scope`; reverted byte-for-byte, resynced, 26/26 green again. cap07 (generated documentation) -- CLOSED (pre-existing from the phase-1 skeleton commit 4b4e16bbb, reconfirmed live this pass by reading its content): docs/rmcp_reference.md is a genuine SPARQL-SELECT-projected markdown table over all 4 classes (rmcp:HandlerMethod/rmcp:Macro/rmcp:Transport/rmcp:Feature), not hand-written prose describing generated code after the fact. cap09 (generated receipts) -- CLOSED 2026-07-21 (commit fcff3b05c): examples/rmcp-verify wired into scripts/ci/guard-pack-proofs.sh's CONSUMERS array. Independently re-verified in this census pass (not just re-running the prior phase's claim): ran the full script fresh against a rebuilt debug ggen binary (26.7.28) across all 5 wired consumers -- `guard-pack-proofs: OK (5 consumers: sync clean, idempotent, receipt valid+signed, all generated proofs pass)`; separately confirmed via a direct `ggen receipt verify` against examples/rmcp-verify's live .ggen-v2/receipt.json: `{\"valid\": true, \"outputs\": 11, \"signed\": true, \"signature_valid\": true}`. guard-pack-proofs is already a `just pre-commit` dependency, so this is reachable from the Definition of Done." ;
    l5p:missingCap l5p:cap01, l5p:cap02, l5p:cap08, l5p:cap10, l5p:cap11, l5p:cap12 ;
    l5p:nextPromotionObligation "6 capabilities remain open, none closed in this census pass (adjudication/reconciliation only). cap01 (authoritative semantic source) -- real, disclosed gap: rmcp_stub_handler.rs.tmpl's `echo` tool's name/description/return string are template-authored facts with no backing ontology individual (the ontology models rmcp's real API surface, not this pack's own demo tool's business logic) -- same shape as affidavit-pack's own disclosed cap01 gap, smaller in surface area. cap02 (complete generation surface) -- the consumer still needs one hand-written `include!(\"rmcp_lib_wiring.rs\");` line in src/lib.rs -- the same universal gap every domain pack in this census carries (pack_clap_noun_verb, pack_praxis_core, pack_star_toml, pack_lsp_max all list it too); no accepted repo precedent closes it yet. cap08 (generated provenance) -- .ggen-v2/receipt.json's closure map hashes every ontology/template file touched globally per sync run, not a per-generated-artifact trace (confirmed by reading the live receipt) -- matches the universal census gap named in pack_praxis_core's own nextPromotionObligation. cap10 (generated release surface) -- no packaging/CI templates exist for rmcp-pack itself; would need a new template category (cf. tcps-release-pack's CI-YAML generation, the only pack in this census that has one). cap11 (generated evolution path) -- no automated diffing tool surfaces upstream rmcp API changes as a semantic diff; this pass only demonstrated (via the cap05/cap06 drift-sensitivity edits) that an ontology-level change propagates through resync with refusal-then-remediation, not an unattended semantic-diff loop. cap12 (consumer replacement) -- blocked on cap02: the cap04 erase-and-rebuild evidence is necessary but not sufficient for cap12's stronger 'from ggen.toml + the pack alone, zero hand-authored file' bar while the include! line remains required." .

