    l5p:currentCeiling "First-ever adjudication (2026-07-21, cell-f census). cap03 (deterministic regen) -- holds live: a real root `ggen sync run --dry-run` against this checkout today reports all 5 of this pack's outputs (`.github/workflows/publish-candidate.yml`, `.github/workflows/marketplace-docs.yml`, `RELEASE_STANDING.json`, `RELEASE_STANDING.md`, `docs/PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT.md`) as `skipped: unchanged: content identical`; `composed_packs_e2e.rs` (2/2 passing, re-run live in this reconciliation pass) independently confirms idempotence as part of a real 30/31-pack union, though its own spot-check list covers 6 OTHER packs, not this one. Correction to cell-f's original census (this reconciliation pass independently re-ran the claim rather than trusting either the cell or the wave's own auditor): the pack's only dedicated proof, `crates/ggen-engine/tests/ggen_release_pack_workflow_e2e.rs` (the sole test anywhere naming PublishCandidateWorkflow/RELEASE_STANDING/PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT/marketplace-docs.yml), is GREEN, not red. Cell-f's original report claimed '0/2 -- currently RED' with an `[FM-CONFIG-002]` schema-dispatch failure; that specific claim did NOT reproduce and is corrected here rather than passed through. The wave's independent auditor re-ran it 3 times fresh against a clean build and got 2/2 every time; this reconciliation pass independently re-ran it 3 more times on top of that (6 consecutive green runs total, across two independent sessions) -- `marketplace_docs_workflow_regenerates_byte_identical_to_committed_file` and `marketplace_docs_workflow_second_sync_is_idempotent` both pass consistently, no FM-CONFIG-002 seen. Per this repo's own CLAUDE.md note that builds can flap nondeterministically under concurrent worktree sessions, the most plausible account is a transient environment artifact specific to cell-f's own worktree session at the time -- not a diagnosed code defect, and not reproducible now. cap05 (generated verification) -- the pack's cleare